00:55:12.460 --> 00:55:15.890
And as far as I can tell,

00:55:15.890 --> 00:55:20.020
his friends in college
do not go on dates.

00:55:20.020 --> 00:55:23.410
The younger generation
does not go on dates.

00:55:23.410 --> 00:55:24.710
Now, how sad is that?

00:55:24.710 --> 00:55:26.010
Now, it's just interesting.

00:55:26.010 --> 00:55:27.790
They had a lot of sex
as far as I can tell.

00:55:27.790 --> 00:55:29.970
And that's the exact opposite.

00:55:29.970 --> 00:55:31.270
When I was in college, you know,

00:55:31.270 --> 00:55:32.980
that getting the sex part
was the hard part to get.

00:55:32.980 --> 00:55:34.430
But going on a date
was easy, you know.

00:55:34.430 --> 00:55:37.760
It is flip flop now where
there are a lot of people

00:55:37.760 --> 00:55:39.130
out there hungry for romance.

00:55:39.130 --> 00:55:45.380
A lot of people in the younger
generation I believe are hungering

00:55:45.380 --> 00:55:47.760
for romance.

00:55:47.760 --> 00:55:50.170
And that's why they go into
this country western music

00:55:50.170 --> 00:55:53.480
or these old jazz songs
because the romantic ethos

00:55:53.480 --> 00:55:56.040
of that music expresses
something they want to know

00:55:56.040 --> 00:55:58.540
like it's hard to find nowadays.

00:55:58.540 --> 00:56:02.420
That's a controversial view
but that's what I believe.

00:56:02.420 --> 00:56:04.360 position:56%
