your thoughts about the role

00:58:24.720 --> 00:58:26.570
of Jewish-American composers

00:58:26.570 --> 00:58:30.790
in establishing the body
of American love songs?

00:58:30.790 --> 00:58:32.560
&gt;&gt; Ted Gioia: Well,
they had a huge role.

00:58:32.560 --> 00:58:35.730
They had I mean, because
if you look at the people

00:58:35.730 --> 00:58:41.000
that really pioneered the American
love song, it tended to be people

00:58:41.000 --> 00:58:43.050
like the Gershwin Brothers,
George and Ira,

00:58:43.050 --> 00:58:44.850
Irving Berlin, you
just go on and on.

00:58:44.850 --> 00:58:48.300
Harold Arnold was the-- it was
the Jewish songwriters who tapped

00:58:48.300 --> 00:58:51.390
into the African-American
jazz stuff.

00:58:51.390 --> 00:58:54.350
And I understood that
they mixed it in with many

00:58:54.350 --> 00:58:56.600
of their own musical traditions
and there's a huge amount

00:58:56.600 --> 00:58:59.630
of Jewish music that filtered into
popular music or [inaudible] music,

00:58:59.630 --> 00:59:02.360
but you can hear that filtering in.

00:59:02.360 --> 00:59:04.670
And it's interesting
even, take Cole Porter,

00:59:04.670 --> 00:59:09.100
he was one of the few songwriters
there who wasn't Jewish.

00:59:09.100 --> 00:59:12.170
And he was having a conversation
with someone once and he said,

00:59:12.170 --> 00:59:14.090
"I'm going to write Jewish songs".

00:59:14.090 --> 00:59:15.390
That's right, I'm going
to write Jewish.

00:59:15.390 --> 00:59:18.960
That was his idea how to
write a love song in America.

00:59:18.960 --> 00:59:22.770
So it was this extraordinary,
but really, it was--

00:59:22.770 --> 00:59:24.750
I'm going to go to this whole thing

00:59:24.750 --> 00:59:28.940
where I say the outsider
has more freedom to sing

00:59:28.940 --> 00:59:32.030
about new ways of love
than the inside.

00:59:32.030 --> 00:59:37.970
If you are a member of the ruling
class, you have to be respectable.

00:59:37.970 --> 00:59:39.270 position:56%
You're a member of the ruling class,

00:59:39.270 --> 00:59:41.770
you have to watch everything
you do or say.

00:59:41.770 --> 00:59:44.750
And so the members of the ruling
class are never good at tapping

00:59:44.750 --> 00:59:46.650 position:56%
